FBIS4-17532 "drsov079_v_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-079 Daily Report 24 Apr 1994 Lithuania President Sends Condolences on Nixon Death President Sends Condolences on Nixon Death LD2404122394 Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network in Lithuanian 1100 GMT 24 Apr 94 LD2404122394 Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network Lithuanian BFN [Text] Lithuanian President Algirdas Brazauskas sent a telegram to Washington expressing his condolences after the death of former U.S. President Richard Nixon, ELTA reported. The telegram stresses that Richard Nixon was one of the first world-ranking politicians to visit independent Lithuania, promoting in every possible way the reinforcement of human rights and democracy in the restored state.
